org.sbml.squeezer

Interface OptionsGeneral

  • All Superinterfaces:
    de.zbit.util.prefs.KeyProvider

    public interface OptionsGeneral
extends de.zbit.util.prefs.KeyProvider
    This is a list of possible command line options and configuration of SBMLsqueezer. Each element listed here determines a key for a configuration value.
    Since:
    2.0
    Author:
    Andreas Dräger, Sarah R. Müller vom Hagen, Sebastian Nagel

      • ALL_REACTIONS_AS_ENZYME_CATALYZED

        static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> ALL_REACTIONS_AS_ENZYME_CATALYZED
        If true, all reactions within the network are considered enzyme reactions. If false, an explicit enzymatic catalyst must be assigned to a reaction to obtain this status.

      • IGNORE_THESE_SPECIES_WHEN_CREATING_LAWS

        static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<String> IGNORE_THESE_SPECIES_WHEN_CREATING_LAWS
        Allows the user to ignore species that are annotated with the given compound identifiers when creating rate laws for reactions that involve these species. For instance, water or single protons can often be ignored when creating rate equations, hence simplifying the resulting rate equations. Preselected are the KEGG compound identifiers for water and protons.

      • REMOVE_UNNECESSARY_PARAMETERS_AND_UNITS

        static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> REMOVE_UNNECESSARY_PARAMETERS_AND_UNITS
        If true parameters and units that are never referenced by any element of the model are deleted when creating kinetic equations with SBMLsqueezer.

      • SET_BOUNDARY_CONDITION_FOR_GENES

      • POSSIBLE_ENZYME_MACROMOLECULE

        static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<Boolean> POSSIBLE_ENZYME_MACROMOLECULE
        If this options is selected, species that are annotated as macromolecules are treated as enzymes when catalyzing a reaction. Otherwise, macormolecule-catalyzed reactions are not considered enzyme reactions. If a modifier of a reaction that is annotated as an enzymatic catalyst refers to a macromolecule but this option is not active, SBMLsqueezer will reduce the modifier to a simple catalyst.

      • TYPE_UNIT_CONSISTENCY

        static final de.zbit.util.prefs.Option<UnitConsistencyType> TYPE_UNIT_CONSISTENCY
        How to ensure unit consistency in kinetic equations? One way is to set each participating species to an initial amount and to set the unit to mmole. The other way is to set the initial concentration of each species, set the unit to mmole per l and to multiply the species with the size of the surrounding compartment whenever it occurs in a kinetic equation. Hence, this type parameter belongs to two values.
